snippet.textDisplay: Great result for Leeds United...the Whites have bounced back impressively from that sticky patch. You clinically despatched Hull and got assistance from Wigan beating The Shit, too...that's a turnaround of a massive +5 on the goal difference front, so not a bad day's work for LUFC. Four clean sheets on the bounce aint to be sniffed at, either. You've now got one whole foot and a couple of toes in the Premier League, so relax, keep backing your team, and enjoy the run-in. Last year's heartache will soon be forgotten, so best wishes, guys, keep the faith...and see you in the Prem very soon. It'll be good to have you back. WOLVES AY WE 🐺🏴󠁧󠁢󠁥󠁮󠁧󠁿🐺🏴󠁧󠁢󠁥󠁮󠁧󠁿🐺🏴󠁧󠁢󠁥󠁮󠁧󠁿🐺

snippet.textDisplay: Goodbye, Bamford. Hello Tyler Roberts! Welcome back. That's how the results should have been for months now. Let's hope that will get their confidence flowing for the rest of the season. This was a significant win! Could have been 7, but 4 is absolutely perfect. I think people were knocking Costa too hard. He's in the picture and looks very dangerous. Hernandez has kept this team together during the wobbly spell. He's a seasoned pro and his vision is brilliant. Can't say enough about the man. It's all yours now Leeds. Get up there!
